```class Solution {
public:
    int countDigitOne(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n != 0) {
            count += n % 10;
            n /= 10;
        }
        return count;
    }
};```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:
The solution uses a while loop to iterate through the digits of the number n starting from the rightmost digit. In each iteration, it adds the current digit to the count and removes the digit by dividing n by 10. This approach has a time complexity of O(log(n)) due to the iterative process of removing digits. The solution uses a constant amount of space (O(1)) and has low energy implications since it only performs a few arithmetic operations.

